            <title><![CDATA[Centering Text Inside a Button]]></title>
            <link>https://actionanand.github.io/wiki/blog/text-align-center-in-button</link>
            <guid>https://actionanand.github.io/wiki/blog/text-align-center-in-button</guid>
            <pubDate>Thu, 08 Feb 2024 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[Instead of centering headings and paragraphs, let’s center text inside another element ( ). Aligning the button, and the text inside the button, would differ slightly from the examples.]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Instead of centering headings and paragraphs, let’s center text inside another element (<code>&lt;button&gt; &lt;/button&gt;</code>). Aligning the button, and the text inside the button, would differ slightly from the examples.</p>
<p>That’s because the text-align property only works on the content inside block-level elements, such as headings and paragraphs, and not inline elements, such as buttons.</p>
<p>So here's what we'll do instead:</p>
<ul>
<li>Wrap the button in a <code>div</code></li>
<li>Then, add an inline style declaration to the div, i.e. <code>&lt;div style="text-align:center"&gt;</code>.</li>
</ul>
